{"eventId":"evt_6d7e8f9a0c","eventType":"claim_removed","claimId":"clm_aca_010","fromRevisionId":1280000129,"toRevisionId":1280000130,"section":"Impact","before":"The ACA's Cadillac tax on high-cost employer health plans was expected to generate $87 billion in revenue over ten years and slow the growth of healthcare costs by discouraging overly generous plans.","after":"","deterministicFacts":[{"fact":"The Cadillac tax claim was removed from the Impact section.","detail":"The Cadillac tax was fully repealed by the Further Consolidated Appropriations Act of 2020 (signed December 2019). The claim had been tagged with {{update}} since January 2020."},{"fact":"The removal was accompanied by a note directing readers to the 'Legislative history' section for the repeal timeline.","detail":"The Impact section was updated to reflect only currently operative provisions."}],"modelInterpretation":{"semanticChange":"Removed a provision that had been fully repealed, eliminating a potential source of reader confusion about active policy.","confidence":0.97,"discussionType":"policy_update"},"layer":"observed","timestamp":"2025-03-05T09:45:51Z"}
